newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-Woodside Sept qtr sales A$184.9 mln.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-Woodside Sept qtr sales A$184.9 mln.

text.p: Woodside Petroleum Ltd said on Wednesday sales revenue totalled A$184.9 million in the three months ended September 30, 1996.
Sales in the 1995 September quarter were A$151.4 million.
Woodside, 40 percent owned by the Royal Dutch/Shell Group, said its capital expenditure was A$28.1 million for the September quarter and exploration expenditure was A$19.9 million in the quarter.
Woodside is the operator of the North West Shelf gas project offshore Western Australia.
